CONCERN is growing for a missing teenage girl who has disappeared from her home.Riannon (corr) McGuiness, 13, was last seen in Clydebank on Sunday.Her father Paul said her disappearance was &quot;out of character&quot; and appealed for help in tracing her.Riannon's relatives said they were becoming increasingly concerned about her and made a public appeal on social media for information.It is understood the 13-year-old was last seen in the Parkhall area of Clydebank at around 1.45pm on Sunday.